{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F2i9ARcMDH4t7jZZDvZJ7z","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a complete report of all four items.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `verify_integrity` section of the `tapps_memory` handler\n\nFile: `/mnt/c/cursor/TappMCP/packages/tapps-mcp/src/tapps_mcp/server_memory_tools.py`\n\n**Lines 1575-1631** — the full `_handle_verify_integrity` function:\n\n```python\n# line 1575\ndef _handle_verify_integrity(store: MemoryStore, _p: _Params) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Handle the verify_integrity action -- check memory entries for tampering.\n\n    Delegates to ``store.verify_integrity()`` for HMAC-SHA256 verification\n    when available. Falls back to a basic consistency check (entry round-trip)\n    for older tapps-brain versions.\n    \"\"\"\n    if hasattr(store, \"verify_integrity\") and callable(store.verify_integrity):\n        result = store.verify_integrity()\n        return {\n            \"action\": \"verify_integrity\",\n            \"total_entries\": result[\"total\"],\n            \"verified\": result[\"verified\"],\n            \"tampered\": result[\"tampered\"],\n            \"no_hash\": result[\"no_hash\"],\n            \"tampered_keys\": result[\"tampered_keys\"][:20],\n            \"missing_hash_keys\": result.get(\"missing_hash_keys\", [])[:20],\n            \"tampered_details\": result.get(\"tampered_details\", [])[:10],\n            \"integrity_method\": \"hmac_sha256\",\n            \"store_metadata\": _store_metadata(store),\n        }\n\n    # Fallback for older tapps-brain without verify_integrity()\n    import hashlib\n\n    entries = store.list_all()\n    total = len(entries)\n    tampered: list[str] = []\n    verified = 0\n\n    for entry in entries:\n        fetched = store.get(entry.key)\n        if fetched is None:\n            tampered.append(entry.key)\n            continue\n\n        expected = hashlib.sha256(\n            f\"{entry.key}|{entry.value}|{entry.tier}\".encode()\n        ).hexdigest()[:16]\n        actual = hashlib.sha256(\n            f\"{fetched.key}|{fetched.value}|{fetched.tier}\".encode()\n        ).hexdigest()[:16]\n\n        if expected == actual:\n            verified += 1\n        else:\n            tampered.append(entry.key)\n\n    return {\n        \"action\": \"verify_integrity\",\n        \"total_entries\": total,\n        \"verified\": verified,\n        \"tampered\": len(tampered),\n        \"tampered_keys\": tampered[:20],\n        \"integrity_method\": \"sha256_roundtrip\",\n        \"store_metadata\": _store_metadata(store),\n    }\n```\n\nTwo paths:\n- **Happy path (tapps-brain >= current):** delegates to `store.verify_integrity()` which uses HMAC-SHA256, reports `integrity_method: \"hmac_sha256\"`.\n- **Fallback (older tapps-brain):** does a SHA-256 round-trip check on key+value+tier, reports `integrity_method: \"sha256_roundtrip\"`, and lacks `no_hash`/`missing_hash_keys`/`tampered_details` fields.\n\n---\n\n## 2. No separate `memory_health` / `_handle_health` function\n\nThere is no `_handle_health` or `memory_health` function in `server_memory_tools.py`. The file contains no such handler. The nearest thing is `_handle_maintain` (line 1487) and `_handle_safety_check` (line 1545). The dispatch table (`_DISPATCH`, lines 1810-1840) confirms `\"verify_integrity\"` and `\"safety_check\"` are the two M1 security surface entries — no `health` action exists.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `verify_integrity` in tapps-brain\n\nFile: `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py`, **lines 1371-1433** — method on `MemoryStore`:\n\n```python\ndef verify_integrity(self) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Scan all entries and verify their HMAC integrity hashes.\n\n    For each entry that has a stored ``integrity_hash``, recomputes the\n    HMAC-SHA256 and checks for a match. Entries without a stored hash\n    (pre-v8 or NULL) are reported separately.\n\n    Returns:\n        Dict with ``total``, ``verified``, ``tampered``, ``no_hash``,\n        ``tampered_keys``, ``missing_hash_keys``, ``tampered_details``.\n    \"\"\"\n    from tapps_brain.integrity import compute_integrity_hash, verify_integrity_hash\n\n    self._metrics.increment(\"store.verify_integrity\")\n\n    with self._lock:\n        entries = list(self._entries.values())\n\n    total = len(entries)\n    verified = 0\n    tampered: list[str] = []\n    tampered_details: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    missing_hash_keys: list[str] = []\n\n    for entry in entries:\n        stored_hash = getattr(entry, \"integrity_hash\", None)\n        if not stored_hash:\n            missing_hash_keys.append(entry.key)\n            continue\n\n        tier_str = entry.tier.value if hasattr(entry.tier, \"value\") else str(entry.tier)\n        source_str = (\n            entry.source.value if hasattr(entry.source, \"value\") else str(entry.source)\n        )\n        if verify_integrity_hash(\n            entry.key, entry.value, tier_str, source_str, stored_hash\n        ):\n            verified += 1\n        else:\n            tampered.append(entry.key)\n            expected = compute_integrity_hash(entry.key, entry.value, tier_str, source_str)\n            tampered_details.append({\n                \"key\": entry.key,\n                \"stored_hash\": stored_hash,\n                \"expected_hash\": expected,\n            })\n            logger.warning(\"integrity_verification_failed\", key=entry.key, tier=tier_str)\n\n    return {\n        \"total\": total,\n        \"verified\": verified,\n        \"tampered\": len(tampered),\n        \"no_hash\": len(missing_hash_keys),\n        \"tampered_keys\": tampered,\n        \"missing_hash_keys\": missing_hash_keys,\n        \"tampered_details\": tampered_details,\n    }\n```\n\nThe underlying hash logic lives in `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/integrity.py`, **lines 116-141**:\n\n```python\ndef verify_integrity_hash(\n    key: str, value: str, tier: str, source: str,\n    stored_hash: str, *, signing_key: bytes | None = None,\n) -> bool:\n    expected = compute_integrity_hash(key, value, tier, source, signing_key=signing_key)\n    return hmac.compare_digest(expected, stored_hash)\n```\n\nThe canonical string used for HMAC-SHA256 is `f\"{key}|{value}|{tier}|{source}\"` (line 112). The function is also re-exported from `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/__init__.py` line 82.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `MemoryStore` import and usage in `server_memory_tools.py`\n\n**Import (lines 24-30)** — under `TYPE_CHECKING` only (so it is a type-only import at runtime):\n\n```python\n# line 24\nif TYPE_CHECKING:\n    from collections.abc import Callable\n    from mcp.server.fastmcp import FastMCP\n    from tapps_core.memory.models import MemoryEntry\n    from tapps_core.memory.store import MemoryStore   # line 30\n```\n\n`tapps_core.memory.store` is itself a thin re-export shim:\n\n```python\n# /mnt/c/cursor/TappMCP/packages/tapps-core/src/tapps_core/memory/store.py\nfrom tapps_brain.store import MemoryStore as MemoryStore   # line 4\n```\n\nSo the actual class is `tapps_brain.store.MemoryStore`. At runtime in `server_memory_tools.py`, the concrete store instance is obtained by calling `_get_memory_store()` (imported from `tapps_mcp.server_helpers`, line 18), and every handler function receives it as its first argument typed `store: MemoryStore`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3ad8402907011a5f (use SendMessage with to: 'a3ad8402907011a5f' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 38584\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 272050</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e34ce78-cb66-445c-866e-bb03bec88fd3","uuid":"d6d2b3bf-34a5-4ff9-9981-ca126f1b507b","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:23:52.674Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the TappsMCP codebase for these things (medium thoroughness):\n\n1. Find the `tapps_memory` tool handler in `packages/tapps-mcp/src/tapps_mcp/server_memory_tools.py` — specifically the section handlin